    <li>The <em>Telemedicine Practice Guidelines 2020</em> explicitly authorize online consultations and prescriptions by registered doctors</li>
    <li><strong>List A drugs</strong> (antibiotics, antihistamines, common medications) can be prescribed immediately</li>
    <li><strong>List B drugs</strong> (insulin, blood pressure meds, thyroid meds) can be prescribed after prior consultation</li>
    <li><strong>Schedule H drugs</strong> (finasteride, testosterone, modafinil, semaglutide) can be prescribed with proper documentation, medical justification, and real-time consultation</li>
    <li><strong>Schedule X drugs</strong> (narcotics, cannabis) are prohibited</li>
    <li>All consultations require informed written consent, secure encryption, documented medical history, and record retention for 3+ years</li>
    <li>Your medical data is protected under the <em>Digital Personal Data Protection Act 2023</em></li>
