    </details>
  </li>

  <li class="faq-item">
    <details>
      <summary>What if I need in-person examination? Can a telemedicine doctor refuse?</summary>
      <div class="faq-ans"><p>No. Under the guidelines, if a doctor determines that in-person examination is necessary, they must refer you to an in-person provider. You also have the right to request an in-person consultation at any time. Telemedicine is an option, not a requirement.</p></div>
    </details>
  </li>

